Each of the Programs above may result in recommendations ranging from capital improvements to routine maintenance of the plant.  Work Orders/Service Calls are established in parallel to identified needs.  Current planned changes to improve safety were the result of the PHA held 3/10/2009, and include:

?    Refresh NFPA Diamonds and Emergency Contact Labeling;
?    Protect transfer hoses and pump by adding more barriers in strategic locations;
?    Clean critical piping (maintenance);
?    Re-paint color-coding
?    Review, fine-tune and expand transfer system SOP?s

These measures were completed by May of 2009.
